✅ 1. Create Maven Project in Git
  
📍 Commands (VS Code Terminal)
git init
mkdir -p src/main/java/com/example
mkdir -p src/test/java/com/example
touch pom.xml
touch src/main/java/com/example/App.java
touch src/test/java/com/example/AppTest.java
  
📍 pom.xml (write inside pom.xml)
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>simple-maven-app</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.13.2</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
</project>
  
✅ 2. Implement Java Program (Simple Calculator)
  
📍 App.java (write here)
package com.example;
public class App {
    public int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        App obj = new App();
        System.out.println("Sum: " + obj.add(5, 3));
    }
}

📍 AppTest.java (write here)
package com.example;
import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.*;
public class AppTest {
    @Test
    public void testAdd() {
        App obj = new App();
        assertEquals(8, obj.add(5, 3));
    }
}

✅ 3. Push and Clone Repository
  
📍 Commands
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Maven project"
git remote add origin <repo-url>
git push -u origin main
  
📍 Clone in VS Code
git clone <repo-url>
  
✅ 4. Build Maven Project
  
📍 Commands (VS Code Terminal)
mvn compile      # Compile code
mvn test         # Run test
mvn clean install   # Build project

✔ Output:
.jar file created inside → target/simple-maven-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

  ✅ 5. Create and Run Jenkins Pipeline
📍 Where to write code
👉 Jenkins → New Item → Pipeline → Pipeline Script

📍 Pipeline Code:
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Clone') {
            steps {
                git '<repo-url>'
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn compile'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn test'
            }
        }

        stage('Package') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn clean install'
            }
        }
    }
}
